  system_desc: 'The first lesson of the Takeoffs of Landings Flight Syllabus.',
  overview:
    '\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cb\u003eFlight Lesson\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003eEstimated Lesson Time:\u0026nbsp; 1.5 Hours Ground Training 2.0 Hours Flight Training\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cimg src="https://cirrusapproachherokuprod.blob.core.windows.net/cirruslmsherokuprodcontainer/content-items/images/23158a2f3708d0d6933020ad41e7e0PRACTICE_AREA_normalAbnormSpec_CAPS.png"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cimg src="https://cirrusapproachherokuprod.blob.core.windows.net/cirruslmsherokuprodcontainer/content-items/images/beb2739a73f71904309050e975e24cCOLOR KEY SKINNY.png"\u003e\u003cb style="background-color: transparent;"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cb style="background-color: transparent;"\u003eLesson Overview\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003eThis lesson focuses on strengthening your stick-and-rudder skills while on approach and departure. The lesson gets started by briefly reviewing some of the critical takeoff and landing flight profiles before you and your instructor take to the skies. Much of the flight is spent either at the practice area or in the traffic pattern. While in the practice area, you\'ll review maneuvers that best demonstrate the low energy-state flight characteristics experienced during takeoff and landing. Those maneuvers will come in handy as you return to the airport and practice every type of approved landing in your Cirrus.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in"\u003eThis is the only lesson within this\ncourse. So be sure to walk away feeling comfortable and confident with your\nlandings before calling it a day.\u0026nbsp; \u003co:p\u003e\u003c/o:p\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in"\u003e\u003co:p\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/o:p\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in"\u003eTasks introduced for the first time are\nindicated in \u003cb\u003eBOLD\u003c/b\u003e. Tasks indicated as PERFORM must be performed without\nassistance from your instructor, as pilot-in-command.\u003co:p\u003e\u003c/o:p\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cimg src="https://cirrusapproachherokuprod.blob.core.windows.net/cirruslmsherokuprodcontainer/content-items/images/838a1a9d69a898c123c42598aa9bf2TakeoffLandingL1.jpg"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e',
